Detailed Description

A word relation type, such as synonyms, antonyms, etc.

Equality, Hashing, and Copying

WNRelatedWordType instances implement NSObject's hash and isEqual methods, as well as the NSCopying protocol. Instances may be compared by value using NSObject::isEqual: and may be used as a key in NSDictionary.

Member Function Documentation

+ (id) antonym

Return the synonym word relationship type.

Words with opposite meanings (beautiful: ugly).

+ (id) crossReference

Return the cross-reference word relationship type.

A related word; (bobcat: lynx)

+ (id) form

Return the form word relationship type.

Words with the same stem (dog: dogs, dogged, doggish).

+ (id) hyponym

Return the hyponym word relationship type.

A word that is more specific (‘chair’ is a hyponym of ‘furniture’).

+ (id) sameContext

Return the same context word relationship type.

Shows relationships between words which are often used in the same manner. For instance "cheeseburger" and "pizza" are often used the same way. Both also taste great.

+ (id) synonym

Return the synonym word relationship type.

Words with very similar meanings (beautiful: pretty).

+ (id) variant

Return the variant word relationship type.

A different spelling for the same word: color and colour are variants.

+ (id) verbForm

Return the verb form word relationship type.

Given a verb such as "run", the verb forms include "running", "ran", and "runs."

+ (id) verbStem

Return the verb stem word relationship type.

Given a verb such as "running", the stem is "run."
